from multi-level feature extraction by implementing filters at various sizes (e.g. 1x1, 3x3, 5x5) in the same layer of the network. This allow the network to capture information at various scales and complexities. [3]</span></div></font>" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;fillColor=none;strokeColor=none;verticalAlign=top;" parent="1" vertex="1"> <mxGeometry x="1719" y="520" width="960" height="100" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="GyPuIFIZT9y83Gh9MrGp-1" value="<div><font style="font-size: 16px;"><u>Depth concatenation</u></font></div><div><br></div><font style="font-size: 13px;"><div style="text-align: justify;"><span style="background-color: initial;">The output of all filters and the pooling layer concatenated along the channel dimension before fed to the next layer. This concatenation ensures that the subsequent layers can access features extracted at different scales. [3]</span></div></font>" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;fillColor=none;strokeColor=none;verticalAlign=top;" parent="1" vertex="1"> <mxGeometry x="1719" y="945" width="960" height="100" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="GyPuIFIZT9y83Gh9MrGp-2" value="<div><font style="font-size: 16px;"><u>Convolution</u></font></div><div><br></div><span style="font-size: 13px;">As explained by the authors in their paper [1] all the convolution use rectified linear activation (ReLU).</span>" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;fillColor=none;strokeColor=none;verticalAlign=top;" parent="1" vertex="1"> <mxGeometry x="1720.87" y="240" width="960" height="70" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="GyPuIFIZT9y83Gh9MrGp-3" value="<div><font style="font-size: 16px;"><u>Global average pooling</u></font></div><div><br></div><font style="font-size: 13px;"><div style="text-align: justify;"><span style="background-color: initial;">The global average, used at the end of the network, averages each 7x7 feature map into 1x1. The difference between the global average and a fully connected layer is the number of weights. If a fully connected layer is used on a 1024x7x7 feature maps then there are 1024x7x7x1024 weights.
